In this proclamation, President Donald J. Trump honors and expresses gratitude to the families of military service members who have made the ultimate sacrifice for their country. He acknowledges that these Gold Star families have paid a great price for the nation's freedom and that their loved ones did not die in vain. The President recognizes the compassion, courage, determination, and strength of these families, many of whom have turned their sorrow into action and community outreach. He emphasizes the importance of standing with these families and ensuring they receive the care, compassion, and respect they deserve. The President proclaims September 24, 2017, as Gold Star Mother's and Family's Day and calls upon all government officials to display the flag of the United States over government buildings on this day. He also encourages the American people to display the flag and hold appropriate ceremonies to show gratitude and respect for these Gold Star Mothers and Families.